# Version Bump Rule (ridelogger-mcp)

## On Every Code Change

When you modify any **source code** in ridelogger-mcp, **increment the patch version** in **both** places (mora da ostane usklađeno):

1. `pyproject.toml` → `[project]` → `version = "x.y.z"`
2. `src/ridelogger_mcp/__init__.py` → `__version__ = "x.y.z"`

Primer: `0.1.1` → `0.1.2` → `0.1.3` …

## Exceptions

Do NOT bump version for:

- Documentation-only changes (README, comments)
- Config that does not affect runtime behavior
- Whitespace/formatting fixes
- Changes only under `.cursor/` pravila koja ne prate izmene u `src/` (ako menjaš samo AI pravila bez koda — bez bump-a)

## Git Tag on Commit

Ako u repou postoji post-commit hook koji taguje `v{version}` (kao u drugim projektima), commituj izmene verzije **zajedno** sa izmenama koda da tag odgovara verziji.
